column5: anywhere still have docks in the water? looking for a decent launch  would like to to fish kawarthas or Gbay
How far you wanna drive ...try Britt hwy 526 ..you don't have to go far from the launch and if there willing there usually decent size

Water is back to normal median on GBay, so no need for docks at launch. Midland has a board walk beside the launch and with that said as of Wednesday the dock beside it was still in. You are in need of a parking permit if you have a trailer though, but not sure anyone actually checks this time of year.
the launch at Muskies Landing is pretty good and if it gets rough there are lots of sheltered areas to fish.(not sure if they still have there docks in)
another vote for Britt...haven't been there since we moved away from Barrie, nice spot and some King Kong muskies
thinking honey harbour possibly. anybody know a launch?  Edit: found one....Village Marina if anybody is wondeirng
